<para id="eip-886">I’ll miss hearing “<term>Howdy</term>” as I walk into our side of the office but you’re off to better things and I wish you the best! :) - Osiris</para><para id="fs-idm496380512">“I will miss Keith’s reassuring presence in the <term>early morning</term> — and he is always helping me find things that need a key --&gt; the owl speaker, cables for the macs, etc. It has been wonderful to lean on his deep Rice experience. ” — Kathi</para>

<para id="fs-idm546361616">“I wish you a happy retirement filled with fun and happiness.  Congratulations and best wishes on your new chapter in life.” - Chan Pham</para>

<para id="fs-idm231891168">Keith, I am wishing you a Happy Retirement!!!<newline/><newline/>

As you reach this time in your life, may you find JOY in remembering past success and HAPPINESS in pursuing new hopes and plans.  Proverbs 16:31 states , ” Gray hair is a crown of glory; it is gained in a righteous life.”<newline/><newline/>

RaKeisha Franklin</para>

<para id="fs-idm950227888">Hello Keith. Words are very hard for me and this dumb website is so slow. Every time it's loading I keep thinking about what I'm going to write but all I keep thinking about is how I keep thinking about what I'm going to write. Anyway. Here are some of my dumb words: Thank you for always being so kind. Thank you for always being so positive. Thank you for laughing at my dumb jokes and thinking that I'm funny. Thank you for listening to me complain about how the sink is full of dishes even though I don't really want to do anything about it. Thank you for listening to me complain about interns eating all of our snacks. I will miss the passing of my expense report back and forth between the two of us because I can't seem to get any of my expenses coded correctly. Anyway, congratulations on retiring! Hopefully one day, I too will get to retire. Maybe when you get bored of your family and traveling, you can come visit us or trade places with me. Best wishes and I hope you have so much fun and so many good things because you deserve it. - Larissa</para>

 
